50|$|Earth has {{an outer}} shell {{made of a}} number of discrete, moving tectonic plates {{floating}} on a solid convective mantle above a liquid core. The mantle's flow is driven by the descent of cold tectonic plates during subduction and the complementary ascent of plumes of <b>hot</b> <b>material</b> from lower levels. The surface of the Earth reflects stretching, thickening and bending of the tectonic plates as they interact.|$|E
