40|$|Abstract: The NLC {{polarized}} positron photon beam {{target is}} a 0. 4 radiation length thick titanium target. Energy deposition from one pulse occurs over 266 nanoseconds {{and results in}} heating of the target and pressure pulses straining the material. The 22. 1 MeV photon beam has a spot size of 0. 75 mm and results in a maximum temperature jump of 233 °C. Stresses are induced in the material from thermal expansion of the <b>hotter</b> <b>material.</b> Peak effective stresses reach 19 ksi (1. 34 x 108 Pa), which {{is lower than the}} yield strength of a titanium alloy by a factor of six...|$|R
50|$|CaB6 {{is highly}} conductive, has low work function, {{and thus can}} be used as a <b>hot</b> cathode <b>material.</b> When used at {{elevated}} temperature, calcium hexaboride will oxidize degrading its properties and shortening its usable lifespan.|$|R
